# SECURITY-TODO #17: assert that members of the `wheel` group must
# authenticate with their password before sudo. This is the Fedora
# default, but it is asserted here at the image layer so the audit
# does not depend on an upstream package's default never changing.
#
# Drop-ins in /etc/sudoers.d/ are processed in alphabetical order; the
# last matching rule wins. The 99- prefix guarantees this file is
# applied after any other Fedora-shipped drop-in, so even if a future
# upstream package landed a NOPASSWD line for %wheel, this file
# overrides it.
#
# Customers who specifically want passwordless sudo for their own user
# can ship their own drop-in (e.g. /etc/sudoers.d/99zz-local-user) but
# must do so deliberately, with knowledge of what they are giving up.
%wheel ALL=(ALL) ALL
